        <div1 type="body">
            
<p><placeName>Alexandria</placeName> <date when="1825-02-02">February the 2nd 1825</date></p>
<p>Dear sir</p>

<p>I beg leave to introduce to your acquaintance <persName>Mr. J. H. Shropsher</persName>
an acquaintance of mine and who you will find to be a gentleman
he is going on to the <placeName> enteria [interior]</placeName> on a trading expedishion he
will want some infirmation of you which I hope you will give all
that you can as I feel much intrusted in his favour and in so 
doing you will confer a remembered [kindness.] Sir agreeable to
promis I expect to come to your <placeName>cuntry</placeName> and am happy to informe
that <persName>Majr. Thomas</persName> his <persNamefather inlaw >Majr. Bullard</persName> and his <persName>brother</persName>
and <persName>Col. Cram</persName> of this place and two or three other <persName>gentlemen </persName>from<pb n="1034"/>
this place will accompany me to look at your <placeName>country </placeName>I feel 
sattisfyed that I shall moove to your <placeName>cuntry</placeName> and beg leave to remind
of your promis to me respecting my land I hope you will he 
perticular in the choice of the <placeName>leage down on the tide watter</placeName> and get it
as low down as posable give my respects to <persName>Col Gross</persName> and <persName>family</persName>
if an opertunity permits</p>

<p><persName>Thos Hooper</persName></p>


        </div1>
